Package gov.tak.api.contact

Interface IGroupContact

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IContact
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GroupContactBase
    public interface IGroupContact
extends IContact
    Represents a group contact, i.e. a group of contacts that can be communicated with via a single group. A group contact can contain a mixture of individual contacts and other group contacts (i.e. nested group contacts).
    Since:
    0.17.0

      • setParentContact

        default void setParentContact​(@Nullable
                              IGroupContact parentContact)
        Sets the parent of a group contact. This method allows for avoiding a "chicken and egg" problem in which a group member must contain a parent contact, and the parent contact must contain said group member.
        Parameters:
        parentContact - The parent contact to set on this group contact
        Since:
        0.55.0
